🟡INTRODUCTION TO CSS

🔻 Cascading Style Sheet
🔻 CSS dscribes the visual style and presentation of the content written in HTML
🔻 CSS consists of countless properties that developers use to format the content : properties about font, text, spacing, layout, etc.

👩‍💻 Code-Snippet

SELECTOR
⬇️
h1 {

PROPERTY ➡️ color: blue;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 20px;
                         ⬆️
                        VALUE
}


🟡INLINE, INTERNAL & EXTERNAL CSS


1. 😆Inline CSS: Styling applied directly within the HTML element.

👩‍💻Code-Snippet

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Inline, Internal & External CSS</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 style="color: blue;">This is styled using inline CSS</h1>
    <p>This is a paragraph.</p>
</body>
</html>


2. 😆Internal CSS: Styling defined within the `<style>` tag in the `<head>` section of the HTML document.

👩‍💻Code-Snippet

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Inline, Internal & External CSS</title>
    <style>
        p {
            color: green;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>This is a heading.</h1>
    <p>This is styled using internal CSS.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

3. 😆External CSS: Styling defined in a separate CSS file and linked to the HTML document.

👩‍💻Code-Snippet

HTML file (index.html):

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Inline, Internal & External CSS</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">
</head>
<body>
    <h1>This is a heading.</h1>
    <p>This is styled using external CSS.</p>
</body>
</html>


CSS file (`styles.css`):


p {
    color: red;
}


These examples demonstrate the usage of inline, internal, and external CSS styles in HTML documents.